body:
@graceguo-supercat I manually tested the filter_immune_slices and it continues to work as expected.

Since the changes I made only really affect the URL and not any internal representation of the filters (`getInitialState` just translates the new URL format to the original internal filter format, while `getDashboardUrl` translates the internal filter format to the new URL format) I hadn't made any changes to how Superset is storing this information. `default_filters` works as it always has and can stay the same going forward.

Do you want `default_filters` for existing and new dashboards updated? If so, a DB migration script is needed as well as changes to how dashboards are saved.
